author: app.com
title: Girls Soccer: Freehold Township wins Class A North rematch with Freehold
text:
MORE There was no double-overtime draw this time.
The No. 4 Freehold Township girls soccer team jumped out to a one-goal halftime lead and eventually defeated Freehold, 3-1, in a Class A North game on Wednesday afternoon.
On Sept. 25, the two Class A North rivals battled to a 1-1 tie.
But on Wednesday afternoon, Jasmine Colbert, Nicole Whitley and Paige Farrell made sure there was a definitive result this time for the Patriots (10-1-1, 7-1-1).
Jasmine Colbert scored in the seventh minute after a diagonal ball from her sister Jada Colbert. Whitley scored in the 75th minute after Farrell played a direct kick into the box and Whitley headed the ball into the net. In the 78th minute, Olivia Schwartz played a ball into the box from the right side, and Farrell settled the ball and then shot to the lower left corner for the goal. Freehold Township’s Kaela Chadziutko made three saves.
Freehold’s Ashley Latona played a ball to Ashley Fuentes, who scored in the 44th minute for the Colonials (6-5-1, 5-4-1). Freehold’s Stephanie Moir made 13 saves.
St. John Vianney 2, Manasquan 1: The Lancers fought back from a 1-0 deficit as Kaite DiFrancisco scored both goals in the Class A Central victory.
Red Bank Catholic 7, Long Branch 0: Sophie Demurjian notched a hat trick in a 16-minute span, Jackie Reiger added one goal and three assists and Jackson Robinson made two saves for the Caseys (8-6-2). Long Branch’s Marelyn Herrera made nine saves.
Marlboro 1, Midd. North 0: Rebecca Gorenstine scored in the 86th minute and Sarah Tropper made seven saves as the Mustangs (3-9, 1-7) defeated the Lions (4-7, 2-7) in a Class A North game. Haley Martin (seven saves) and Sophia Goos (seven saves) each played goalie.
